2.1.0 (July 15, 2026)
Bug fix in `EnumSS()`
Allow per-tissue phase maps in `Enum2SS()`

2.0.0 (July 15, 2026)
Rewrite tissue properties to make them more factually correct.
Add `Enum2SS()` so that user can obtain steady-state signal instead of proton density map, which would have more realistic contrast.
Rename `Enum2M0()` to `Enum2PD()`, PD (proton density) should be real-valued, while M0 is complex valued.
Remove cardiac motion amplitude from `Enum2PD()` and add then to `Enum2SS()` to make PD map more consistent with its definition.

1.0.4 (April 4, 2026)
Include `scipy` as a denpendency and add `gxx` as a prerequirement in `README.md`.

1.0.3 (March 31, 2026)
Update examples.

1.0.2 (March 31, 2026)
Update LICENSE, MANIFEST.in, remove requirements.txt.

1.0.1 (March 29, 2026)
Update package description to make it more accurate.